<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1437,1426,1775]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1426,1451]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species has been confused with 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Erlandsson" authorityYear="1971" box="[703,934,1426,1451]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="constrictus">
<emphasis box="[703,934,1426,1451]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Elampus constrictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in older literature. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sahlberg, J." box="[1158,1386,1426,1451]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="94 - 99" refId="ref61428" refString="Sahlberg, J. (1910) Lyhyt katsaus Suomen kulta-ampiaisiin (Chrysidae). Luonnon Ystava, 14, 94 - 99." type="journal article" year="1910">Sahlberg (1910: 99)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Hellen, W." box="[151,363,1462,1487]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="203 - 213" refId="ref55553" refString="Hellen, W. (1920 [&quot; 1919 &quot;]) Uber finlandische Goldwespen. Meddelanden af Societas pro Fauna et Flora Fennica, 46, 203 - 213." type="journal article" year="1920">Hellén (1920: 206)</bibRefCitation>
reported the species from 
<collectingCountry box="[659,744,1462,1487]" name="Finland" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Finland</collectingCountry>
and Russian Fennoscandia, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Borries, H." box="[1108,1314,1462,1487]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="84 - 96" refId="ref52555" refString="Borries, H. (1891) Oversigt over de danske Guldhvepse. (Chrysididae danicae). Entomologiske Meddelelser, 3, 84 - 96." type="journal article" year="1891">Borries (1891: 92)</bibRefCitation>
reported it from 
<collectingCountry box="[218,322,1498,1523]" name="Denmark" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Denmark</collectingCountry>
(as 
<taxonomicName box="[379,593,1498,1523]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Notozus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="productus">
<emphasis box="[379,593,1498,1523]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Notozus productus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). It was at first reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[970,1059,1498,1523]" name="Sweden" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Sweden</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Thomson, C. G." box="[1111,1359,1498,1523]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="101 - 108" refId="ref63409" refString="Thomson, C. G. (1870) Ofversigt af de i Sverige funna arter af Slagtet Chrysis Lin. Opuscula Entomologica, 2, 101 - 108." type="journal article" year="1870">Thomson (1870: 103</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Notozus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="productus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">E. productus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), after which it was mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mocsary, A." box="[675,896,1534,1559]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" refId="ref58906" refString="Mocsary, A. (1889) Monographia Chrysididarum orbis terrarium universi. Musaei Nat. Hungarici Adiuncto, Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae Socio. Typis Societatis Franklinianae, Budapest, 643 pp." type="book" year="1889">Mocsáry (1889: 68</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName box="[945,1122,1534,1559]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Ellampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">
<emphasis box="[945,1122,1534,1559]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Ellampus spina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 
<bibRefCitation author="Aurivillius, C." box="[1148,1386,1534,1559]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref51647" refString="Aurivillius, C. (1911) Svensk insektfauna XIII. Hymenoptera. 2. Guldsteklar. Tubulifera. Entomologisk Tidskrift, 32, 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1911">Aurivillius (1911: 6)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Jansson, A." box="[151,370,1570,1595]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="1 - 81" refId="ref56471" refString="Jansson, A. (1922) Faunistiska och biologiska studier over insektlivet vid Hornsjon pa norra Oland. Arkiv for Zoologi, 14, 1 - 81." type="journal article" year="1922">Jansson (1922: 33</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hellen" authorityYear="1920" box="[427,593,1571,1594]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Notozus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">
<emphasis box="[427,593,1571,1594]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Notozus spina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 1934: 287, as 
<taxonomicName box="[794,1112,1571,1594]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Notozus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="panzeri" variety="spina">
<emphasis box="[794,982,1571,1594]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Notozus panzeri</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1052,1112,1571,1594]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">spina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). All Finnish and Russian Fennoscandian specimens have been checked and found to belong to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Erlandsson" authorityYear="1971" box="[922,1075,1607,1630]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="constrictus">
<emphasis box="[922,1075,1607,1630]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">E. constrictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is most likely that also all the Danish and Swedish published records refer to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Erlandsson" authorityYear="1971" box="[680,834,1643,1666]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Elampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="constrictus">
<emphasis box="[680,834,1643,1666]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">E. constrictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rosa, P. &amp; Soon, V." box="[849,1080,1642,1667]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="5" refId="ref61258" refString="Rosa, P. &amp; Soon, V. (2012) Fauna Europaea: Chrysididae. In: Mitroiu, M. - D. (Ed.), Fauna Europaea: Hymenoptera, version 2. 5. Available from http: // www. faunaeur. org (accessed 1 November 2013)" type="book chapter" year="2012">Rosa &amp; Soon (2012)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hellen" authorityYear="1920" box="[1187,1278,1643,1666]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Notozus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">
<emphasis box="[1187,1278,1643,1666]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">E. spina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1347,1436,1642,1667]" name="Sweden" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Sweden</collectingCountry>
based on an old Swedish specimen deposited in NRM. The specimen was later found to represent a large individual of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mocsary" authorityYear="1914" box="[187,316,1714,1739]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Ellampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foveatus">
<emphasis box="[187,316,1714,1739]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">E. foveatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Apparently 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hellen" authorityYear="1920" box="[475,573,1715,1738]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Notozus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spina">
<emphasis box="[475,573,1715,1738]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">E. spina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a predominantly South European and West Asian species, with some scattered records from central Europe (
<bibRefCitation author="Banaszak, J." box="[587,763,1750,1775]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="1 - 52" refId="ref51772" refString="Banaszak, J. (1980) Zlotolitki Chrysididae. Katalog Fauny Polski, 26, 1 - 52." type="journal article" year="1980">Banaszak 1980</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
